  "prompt": "What is the average electric bill for a 2-bedroom apartment in the Bay Area?",
  "response": "The average electric bill for a 2-bedroom apartment in the Bay Area can vary significantly based on factors such as energy usage, the efficiency of appliances, insulation, and the specific city or part of the Bay Area you are located in. As of 2023, you can generally expect to pay anywhere from $60 to $150 per month. This range can be higher if the apartment has electric heating or if the residents use a lot of electricity. To get a more precise estimate, considering contacting the local utility provider or asking current or past tenants of similar apartments in the area.",
